Subject: Re: [T2] Heating with water - seeking what-if-ideas

You need to worry about where the heat is going when the heater isn't on!
Otherwise, the coolent will boil away!

A better way to go might be a oil-water heat exchanger.  The oil doesn't
get as hot, so it would be easier to get the heat under control.

George Lyle

